      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You should absolutely not change your dosage without consulting your prescribing physician. Warfarin is a powerful medication, and even feeling fine doesn't mean your clotting factors are perfectly balanced. A sudden drop could put you at serious risk for blood clots, so stick to the prescribed 5mg until your doctor says otherwise.",
