      "content": "Tapering on your own is a dangerous gamble with a medication like warfarin. Your blood levels need precise monitoring, not just how you *feel* at the moment. If you want to reduce the dose, you need a professional to check your INR first, which is the only way to know if you can safely drop to 3mg or 2mg.",
      "source": "target",
