      "content": "Your diet is a helpful *factor*, but it doesn't replace lab testing for warfarin management. Feeling cautious is good, but self-adjusting a blood thinner is reckless. To truly optimize your dose, you need a blood test to confirm your INR is stable at a lower level, and only then should you consider a reduction.",
